-- Gazprom, TNK-BP, Rosneft, Raspadskaya: Russia Equity Preview
-- B y   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 2011-02-03T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-03/gazprom-tnk-bp-rosneft-raspadskaya-russia-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close.  The 30-stock Micex Index rose 0.5 percent to 1,765.42.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX): Natural-gas exporters face a “major
debate” this year about how contracts are formulated, including
a possible move away from formulas based on the price of oil,
Fati Birol, the  International Energy Agency ’s chief economist,
said yesterday in Moscow. Gazprom advanced 2.3 percent to 209.58
rubles.    TNK-BP Holding  (TNBP RX): Ukraine’s government will allow
TNK-BP to develop gas deposits trapped in shale rock to help the
country reduce its dependency on imported fuel, First Deputy
Prime Minister Andriy Kluyev said yesterday by e-mail. TNK-BP
was little changed at 85.97 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): Brent crude for March delivery rose
to as much as $102.47 per barrel. Rosneft, Russia’s largest oil
producer, declined 0.5 percent to 258.11 rubles.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX): A new cyclone in Australia may
damage global coal supplies, Steel Business Briefing reported
yesterday.  Raspadskaya  advanced 2.4 percent to 233.35 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
